    "Notes": {
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "The correlation coefficient is calculated as follows:"
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "BlockDirective",
          "data": {
            "lines": {
              "_lines": [
                {
                  "_line": ".. math::",
                  "_number": 2,
                  "_offset": 0
                }
              ]
            },
            "wh": {
              "_lines": [
                {
                  "_line": "",
                  "_number": 3,
                  "_offset": 0
                }
              ]
            },
            "ind": {
              "_lines": [
                {
                  "_line": "    r = \\frac{\\sum (x - m_x) (y - m_y)}",
                  "_number": 4,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "             {\\sqrt{\\sum (x - m_x)^2 \\sum (y - m_y)^2}}",
                  "_number": 5,
                  "_offset": 0
                },
                {
                  "_line": "",
                  "_number": 6,
                  "_offset": 0
                }
              ]
            },
            "directive_name": "math",
            "args0": [
              ""
            ],
            "inner": {
              "inline": [
                {
                  "type": "Words",
                  "data": {
                    "value": "r = \\frac{\\sum (x - m_x) (y - m_y)}          {\\sqrt{\\sum (x - m_x)^2 \\sum (y - m_y)^2}} "
                  }
                }
              ],
              "inner": []
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "where "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Directive",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "m",
                    "_",
                    "x"
                  ],
                  "domain": null,
                  "role": "math"
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " is the mean of the vector "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Directive",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "x"
                  ],
                  "domain": null,
                  "role": "math"
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " and "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Directive",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "m",
                    "_",
                    "y"
                  ],
                  "domain": null,
                  "role": "math"
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " is the mean of the vector "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Directive",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "y"
                  ],
                  "domain": null,
                  "role": "math"
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "."
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "Under the assumption that x and y are drawn from independent normal distributions (so the population correlation coefficient is 0), the probability density function of the sample correlation coefficient r is ([1]_, [2]_)::"
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "BlockVerbatim",
          "data": {
            "lines": {
              "_lines": [
                {
                  "_line": "           (1 - r**2)**(n/2 - 2)",
                  "_number": 15,
                  "_offset": 4
                },
                {
                  "_line": "    f(r) = ---------------------",
                  "_number": 16,
                  "_offset": 4
                },
                {
                  "_line": "              B(1/2, n/2 - 1)",
                  "_number": 17,
                  "_offset": 4
                },
                {
                  "_line": "",
                  "_number": 18,
                  "_offset": 4
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "where n is the number of samples, and B is the beta function.  This is sometimes referred to as the exact distribution of r.  This is the distribution that is used in "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Directive",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "pearsonr"
                  ],
                  "domain": null,
                  "role": null
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " to compute the p-value. The distribution is a beta distribution on the interval [-1, 1], with equal shape parameters a = b = n/2 - 1.  In terms of SciPy's implementation of the beta distribution, the distribution of r is::"
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "BlockVerbatim",
          "data": {
            "lines": {
              "_lines": [
                {
                  "_line": "    dist = scipy.stats.beta(n/2 - 1, n/2 - 1, loc=-1, scale=2)",
                  "_number": 26,
                  "_offset": 4
                },
                {
                  "_line": "",
                  "_number": 27,
                  "_offset": 4
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "The p-value returned by "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Directive",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "pearsonr"
                  ],
                  "domain": null,
                  "role": null
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " is a two-sided p-value.  For a given sample with correlation coefficient r, the p-value is the probability that abs(r') of a random sample x' and y' drawn from the population with zero correlation would be greater than or equal to abs(r).  In terms of the object "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Verbatim",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "dist"
                  ]
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " shown above, the p-value for a given r and length n can be computed as::"
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "BlockVerbatim",
          "data": {
            "lines": {
              "_lines": [
                {
                  "_line": "    p = 2*dist.cdf(-abs(r))",
                  "_number": 35,
                  "_offset": 4
                },
                {
                  "_line": "",
                  "_number": 36,
                  "_offset": 4
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "When n is 2, the above continuous distribution is not well-defined. One can interpret the limit of the beta distribution as the shape parameters a and b approach a = b = 0 as a discrete distribution with equal probability masses at r = 1 and r = -1.  More directly, one can observe that, given the data x = [x1, x2] and y = [y1, y2], and assuming x1 != x2 and y1 != y2, the only possible values for r are 1 and -1.  Because abs(r') for any sample x' and y' with length 2 will be 1, the two-sided p-value for a sample of length 2 is always 1."
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        }
      ],
